AR09 - UN GRAND ESPACE COMMUN

As part of this exercise, we focused on the theme of collective housing. Our work was anchored in a real-life case by examining a project studied by the small commune of Burtigny, Switzerland, for a collective housing initiative in the heart of the village.To achieve this, we began with an initial study phase in which each group analyzed an activity such as cooking, washing, or working, and how these activities were expressed in collective housing projects across different eras and scales.In the second phase, we worked closely with the village residents to imagine a project aligned with the community’s expectations, working across various scales, from site analysis to 1:1 construction details. The main idea of this project was to explore three degrees of privacy articulated within a housing building.